     length += 1\n            else:\n                count += (length * (length + 1)) // 2\n                length = 1\n        \n        # Add the last alternating sequence\n        count += (length * (length + 1)) // 2\n        \n        return count\n```\n\nThis solution iterates through the list `nums` and counts the length of each alternating subarray. When a non-alternating pair is found, it calculates the number of subarrays that can be formed from the previous alternating sequence using the formula `(length * (length + 1)) // 2` and adds it to the total count. After the loop, it adds the subarrays from the last alternating sequence. This approach ensures that all possible alternating subarrays are counted efficiently.", "estimated_date": 1711843200000}